<br>
We need to do whats best for them.  <br>
<br>
I am going to make some points....its going to take some time so forgive the long post.<br>
<br>
The Current foster system is fooked.  My Dad was a foster kid up to 11 years old.  He had a few good places but mostly bad.  He never said he was sexually molested but he was sure as hell abused.  He has told me stories of his past that would make most grown men cry.  I see how some of his personality quirks came to be and I can accept him better now that i know his past.<br>
<br>
My sister got a degree in social work.  She interned with the state...placing foster kids.  She threw stats at me about numbers of sexually abused kids... numbers of those kids that abuse other kids... etc etc.  Its pretty high.<br>
<br>
Now throw in the number of people out there who abuse kids.  Throw in the number that sexually abuse kids.<br>
<br>
Throw in that though I believe some people are born gay ....but also some are a product of their environment...ie sexually abused as children...suffer psychological scars.... etc etc.  Add in that those that were offended against....have a high percentage of offending others.<br>
<br>
Throw in that many of these kids in the foster system have no idea of stability.... sense of family.... sense of right and wrong.  They are already behind the 8 ball in so many aspects psychologially and socially.<br>
<br>
What does this leave you?  A fricking mess for sure.  So...whats most important?  The Kids.  Not only the kids needing placement....but the kids that are already in homes where you are thinking of placing these kids.  Its about kids.  Not about gay people feeling more whole by being parents or whatever.<br>
<br>
Would some Gay couple make great foster parents?  Hell yes.  Are some heterosexuall couples lousy parents....let alone horrific foster parents....hell yes...just watch the news.<br>
<br>
But... how do we decide who gets kids?  How do we evaluate people to make those decisions?  What are the parameters?  What are the likely factors that &quot;may&quot; affect a child placed in one place vs another.  <br>
<br>
Take all of those into consideration and start wiping out blanket approvals of foster care and maybe kids will end up in the right places.<br>
<br>
Do I think Gay couples should be allowed to be foster parents or adopt children?  Not until there is a method of evaluating them to make sure it is a safe environment....but I would hold every heterosexual couple to the same standards.<br>
<br>
If they meet the requirements...then I would bet they are just as capable of being great parents as anyone else.<br>
<br>
The key is going to be what are the standards.  Religion?  Sexual exposure (ie does the couple gay friend bob and his mate flash sex toys and talk about explicit acts in front of the kid?)  Do Gay couples have a tendency to have permiscuous(sp) relationships....does this crush the stability?  Stats wise do they only stay together for short periods of time?  <br>
<br>
There is so much to consider....just saying Gay people deserve it....well isnt going to fly....because this isnt about Gay people....its about kids....and what is best for them.<br>
<br>
Just My opinion.<br>
<br>
Ichi Dahated<br>
<br>
