<br>
What's the difference?  The screening process would certainly take care of either case.<br>
<br>
Going back to stereotypes... <br>
...that some (a very very small minority) gay people dress in drag does not mean they would do so when dropping their kid off at school.  A lot of straight men have crossdressing fetishes as well, this doesn't mean they go out in public that way in inappropriate environments.  There need not be a new &quot;Drag&quot; questionaiire in the screening process just because gay people can adopt as well.<br>
<br>
As &quot;for the kids...&quot;<br>
...certainly these are noble sentiments, and I agree that it should be for the kids as well.  But I am not willing to say that the parents have no stake in these matters and that all of their interests are subsumed to the best interest of the child.<br>
<br>
Under your logic, we would require adoption agencies to accede to the discriminatory inclinations of homophobic people in the community.  This was rejected by the Supreme Court in Palmore v. Sidoti, where the court explicitly rejected the &quot;Best interests of the Child&quot; argument put forth by a divorced father who sought to claim custody over his child because his ex-wife married a black man.  The father argued that by allowing the child to remain with his mother, the child would be made fun of because of her black husband.  <br>
<br>
There the court held, &quot;Private biases may be outside the reach of the law, but the law cannot, directly or indirectly, give them effect.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=robingoodfellow>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/4/03 2:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=831.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/689americanpeacesign.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Case Against Same-Sex Marriage...</span><hr size=1> Itchi:<br>
