<br>
No facetiousness intended.  Whether its some sort of preprogrammed biological/neurological function or a product of what the media has ingrained in the average citizen, society is currently more open to the notion of two women kissing and living in a sexual union than two men - although that is slowly changing.<br>
<br>
Countless teen movies, directly or indirectly, incorporate the notion that two women mingly is sexy, while the majority of mainstream movies (such as the &quot;Rules of Attraction&quot;, which I just recently saw), typically portray that at least one of the men involved in a homoerotic encounter are &quot;confused&quot; or &quot;misguided&quot;.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately both common depictions of homoeroticism/homosexuality are one-dimensional (sorry guys, not ever lesbian duo is just waiting for a man to jump in there and show them a good time, nor is every instance of male-male attraction fraught with one male being straight whilst the other male is sure that he can convert him).  The fact is, however, that the notion of lesbians finds &quot;wider&quot; acceptance.<br>
<br>
And therein lies the pathway to acceptance.<br>
<br>
My sister-in-law, who is younger and arguably &quot;hipper&quot; than my wife and myself, is what I would consider a fairly staunch Catholic.  Her husband comes from a long line of hardcore Irish Catholics.  They live in a very pleasant coastal community along the British Columbia coast and have two sons, ages 2 and 4.<br>
<br>
Some time ago, my sister-in-law began chatting to us about the mid-twenties single mother (boy aged 3) who moved in across the street.  My sister and brother in-law got along very well with this woman and their children played together regularly.  Then one day, a few month later, a friend of the single mother moved in.  Long story short, eventually everyone in the neighborhood came to realize that this was a lesbian couple, who recently got married by the way, raising a child.<br>
<br>
While the ins and outs of the whole issue would take a post longer than anyone wants to read, the upshot is that despite my sister and brother-in-law's hardcore Catholic beliefs, everyone gets along just grand.  Now, how much of this can be attributed to the fact that the couple are lesbians, or to the fact that their household is stable and their child is &quot;well adjusted&quot;, I'd wager it is a bit of the former but primarily due to the latter, which is what truly matters in the end.  <br>
<br>
However despite the apparent social success of this case, of which I have been imparted a large amount of first hand knowledge, I've wondered:  if it were two men, and not two women, would the outcome have been as amiable?  Given some time, hopefully yes.<br>
<br>
If our social programs were properly funded and had enough resources, the approriateness of having a child raised or adopted into any particular household would be measured in depth on a case by case basis - regardless of sexual orientation.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvellu>fvellu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>Big Bad Voodoo Daddy</b></span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/27/03 12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=831.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ItchibumBashalots is wrong.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No facetiousness intended.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> BOOO hisss BOOOO **jeer** <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showMessageRange?topicID=831.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showPrevMessage?topicID=831.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showNextMessage?topicID=831.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=831.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.threadControl?topicID=831.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Top